Got a decent update. As you know, the Fiserv ISO agreement allows them to sell to any merchant that a) is processing over $5mm annually in
Visa/MC volume and b) that they have an existing banking relationship with. We've always known that Fiserv approaches our merchants-
and we've lost a few along the way, although we've never lost a really big one (that i'm aware of).
We're getting more and more feedback from our sales teams about their merchants being approached by Fiserv and them quoting 7-1 Obps.
Seems crazy for them to be that aggressive given they have ~30% of the economics on the portfolio {see revenue share schedule below), but
John is working on some analysis to see what the "average" might look like.
Additionally, John has been calling all of the "top" merchants- specifically those that we believe might meet that $5mm threshold, and is
getting the following feedback:
•    Merchants are confirming that Fiserv is reaching out
•    Merchants are saying that they are tuming down the Fiserv calls.

We're working on a way to better equip our sales teams to battle this head-to-head, and we're working on ways to pull together more
concrete data. But in the meantime, wanted to get the feedback to you while it was "fresh".
Let me know what you think.
